{"questionId":"9073813","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A planet is in a circular orbit around a star. The speed of the planet is constant. The following&nbsp;data are given:</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:120px;\">Mass of planet&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>24</mn></msup><mo> </mo></math>kg<br>Mass of star&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>30</mn></msup><mo> </mo></math>kg<br>Distance from the star to the planet <em>R</em>&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>10</mn></msup><mo> </mo></math>m.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A spacecraft is to be launched from the surface of the planet to escape from the star&nbsp;system. The radius of the planet is 9.1 × 10<sup>3</sup> km.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Show that the gravitational potential due to the planet and the star at the surface&nbsp;of the planet is about −5 × 10<sup>9 </sup>J kg<sup>−1</sup>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em>V</em><sub>planet</sub> = «−»<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>67</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>11</mn></mrow></msup><mo>)</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>24</mn></msup><mo>)</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>6</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo></math>«−» 5.9&nbsp;× 10<sup>7&nbsp;</sup>«J kg<sup>−1</sup>»&nbsp;<strong>✓</strong></p>\n<p><